<br>
Originally, the idea was for Froststone (yes, that is the name of the city in the middle of that dungeon) was supposed to be an alternative newbie city for dwarves. But when Velious was repositioned to be a new hi-level set of zones (rather than newbie-&gt;60 like Kunark), the newbie-ness of CC was gutted, high level mobs placed in there and the quests un-implemented. I am sure that folks prefer it the level appropriate nature that it is now, rather than say CC being a newbie zone (think Cabilis and Field of Bone) and Eastern Wastes being mid teens to 30s zone (think Lake of Ill Omen and Frontier Mountains).<br>
<br>
No, the monsters as they are now would be suicidal for a newb to be in the place, but think orc pawns and spiderlings instead of the buffed mobs there now. <br>
<br>
I do a lot of quests, so I look at NPCs and what drops nearby and see patterns. I am partly saddened (I was not the discoverer) and gladdened (wow, that is well worth getting) by the discovery of the Chardok quests.<br>
<br>
Rhetorical questions meant to get your mind flowing:<br>
What are the purposes of the orc scalps that drop in CC and EW? In my mind it is the equivalent to the orc and gnoll scalps and goblin ears in High hold pass. Where is Capt Orben, Bosec and Capt Ashlan or their equivalent?<br>
What shall we do with all those dang picks that drop in CC? To whom do we hand them 4 at a time? I have tried all the NPCs. There are only so many pets that you can give picks to...<br>
Those eyeballs that the velium crawlers drop look so yummy. NOT. But they do look like there is some NPC somewhere in CC just waiting for them... <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#F5F5DC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/urovellmacsassin.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Rovell MacSassin</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.purgatory.net/ea/rov10x10.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Chakan can't handle this...</span><br>  Posts: 352<br> <font color=#FF0000>(12/3/01 8:16:51 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.purgatory.net/rovell/rovicon.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: CC being unfinished</span><hr size=1> Nice insight tangurena <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CCCCCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uottoemobeel.showPublicProfile?language=EN>OttoeMobeel</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>i am the great lord of digression</span><br>  Posts: 151<br> <font color=#FF0000>(12/3/01 8:44:47 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: CC being unfinished</span><hr size=1> wow, i never knew that tang<br>
<br>
while CC is prolly my favorite zone in all of velious, possibly my favorite in the whole game, it would have been interesting to see it play out like that, and i do remember hearing rumors about there being a new starting city for dwarves (and possibly barbarians?!) in velious, but i heard all that way before it came out, and they prolly just changed their mind becuz it was too hard to implement.<br>
<br>
hehe, EW is such a popular exp zone for the 30-40 crowd, almost like an expansion to loio, and CC is sorta the lowest lvl dungeon that really does have decent risk vs reward, and helps prepare alot of younger folk for their futures in seb and such.<br>
<br>
i know there will be hardcore people coming up saying that certain young dungeons like dalnirs and splitpaw really are great for people who aren't too &quot;wussy&quot; to try them, but seriously, there is not much in the way of real risk vs reward balance in most of those zones(what am i saying? splitpaw gloves are UBER!).  what reason is there for going into most of those dungeons other than to be &quot;cooler than all those geeks in OT&quot;.<br>
<br>
i have explored all of runney eye, most of dalnirs, splitpaw and mistmoore, all at the appropriate lvls, but that sure as heck wasn't where i got all my 15-45 exp, and most people would laff at me if my uber lvl 47 bard equip was a mix of splitpaw leather and blackened iron(or even alloy).<br>
<br>
wow, was that ever a pointless babble. . . . .hehe, obviously i'm in serious withdrawl *twitch*<br>
